      "text": "Research says that 70% of the overall information is taken up via your body language. The body language can either support or contradict the spoken word. During the communication process, the body language always overrides the spoken word, i.e. the use (or not use) of this non-verbal form of communication can significantly affect the whole teaching process.\n  ",
